Shadow Tiddler Discovery

Plugin-bundled tiddlers are "shadow" tiddlers. The default `[tag[]]` operator only searches the main wiki store (real tiddlers), NOT the shadow store.

```
<!-- BROKEN — misses shadow tiddlers from plugins -->
[tag[$:/tags/MyTag]]

<!-- CORRECT — includes both real and shadow tiddlers -->
[all[tiddlers+shadows]tag[$:/tags/MyTag]]
```

When to use `[all[tiddlers+shadows]...]`:

- Any filter that discovers tiddlers by tag where the tagged tiddlers may come from plugins
- Discovery patterns like "list all tiddlers tagged X" where X is a custom tag
- Looking up layout templates, app definitions, tool registrations, or config tiddlers shipped by plugins

When plain `[tag[]]` is fine:

- Searching only user-created content (e.g., diary entries, notes)
- Contexts where you know all matching tiddlers are in the main store

Symptoms of this bug:

- "No items found" even though tagged tiddlers exist inside a plugin
- Dynamic lists that work after editing (overriding) a shadow tiddler but not before
- Features that work in dev (where .tid files are real tiddlers) but break in single-file wiki (where they're shadows)
